There are two types of concurrency structures you need:

- `CountDownLatch` to track completion of all jobs and 
- `Semaphore` to control exclusive access to the limited resource

See an example:

```
private static final int NUM_FLIGHTS = 5;
private static final int RUNWAY_CAPACITY = 1;

public static void main(String[] args) throws InterruptedException {
    Semaphore semaphore = new Semaphore(RUNWAY_CAPACITY);
    CountDownLatch latch = new CountDownLatch(NUM_FLIGHTS);

    for (int i = 0; i &lt; NUM_FLIGHTS; i++) {
        Runway flight = new Runway(i + 1, semaphore, latch);
        new Thread(flight).start();
    }
    latch.await();
    System.out.println(&quot;All flights have been managed.&quot;);
}

private static class Runway implements Runnable {
    private final int flightNum;
    private final Semaphore semaphore;
    private final CountDownLatch latch;

    public Runway(int flightNum, Semaphore semaphore, CountDownLatch latch) {
        this.flightNum = flightNum;
        this.semaphore = semaphore;
        this.latch = latch;
    }

    public void run() {
        try {
            // Wait for runway availability
            semaphore.acquire(1);

            // Land/take off the flight
            if (flightNum % 2 == 0) {
                System.out.println(&quot;Flight &quot; + flightNum + &quot; is taking off [&quot; + Thread.currentThread().getName() + &quot;]&quot;);
            } else {
                System.out.println(&quot;Flight &quot; + flightNum + &quot; is landing [&quot; + Thread.currentThread().getName() + &quot;]&quot;);
            }
        } catch (InterruptedException e) {
            e.printStackTrace();
        } finally {
            // Release the runway
            semaphore.release(1);

            // Notify main thread about completion
            latch.countDown();
        }
    }
}
```

