this may work add this to your security configarations

So basically you need to tell Spring security to permit your api and disable csrf for it.


```java

    @Override
    protected void configure(HttpSecurity http) throws Exception {
        http.authorizeRequests().antMatchers(&quot;/images/**&quot;).permitAll();
        http.authorizeRequests().antMatchers(&quot;/public/**&quot;).permitAll();


        // Permit your api
        // If you don&#39;t need authentication, just use permitAll to /api/**
        http.authorizeRequests()
                .antMatchers(&quot;/api/auth/login&quot;).permitAll()
                .antMatchers(&quot;/api/**&quot;).hasRole(&quot;USER&quot;);


        // Maybe you need token header filter for your api authentication
        // Following other Spring Security tutorial to implement it.
        // https://stackoverflow.com/questions/41975045/how-to-design-a-good-jwt-authentication-filter
        http.addFilterBefore(jwtTokenFilter(), UsernamePasswordAuthenticationFilter.class);

        // Vaadin Security
        super.configure(http);
        setLoginView(http, LoginView.class);

        // IMPORTENT: csrf must disable for Rest API, otherwise post
        // request won&#39;t work
        http.cors().and().csrf().ignoringAntMatchers(&quot;/api/**&quot;);
    }
```

